7 3. To formulate plans for the promotion of career and technical education in such
8 subjects as are an essential and integral part of the public school system of education
9 in this state.
10 4. To provide for the preparation of teachers.
11 5. To fix the compensation of such officers and assistants as may be necessary to
12 administer the federal acts and the provisions of this chapter relating to career and
13 technical education and to pay the same and other necessary expenses of
14 administration from any funds appropriated for such purpose.
15 6. To make studies and investigations relating to career and technical education.
16 7. To promote and aid in the establishment of schools, departments, or classes, and to
17 cooperate with local communities in the maintenance of career and technical
18 education schools, departments, or classes.
19 8. To prescribe the qualifications and provide for the certification of teachers, directors,
20 and supervisors.
21 9. To cooperate with governing bodies of school districts and with organizations and
22 communities in the maintenance of classes for the preparation of teachers, directors,
23 and supervisors of career and technical education, to maintain classes for such
24 purposes under its own direction and control, and to establish and control, by general
25 regulations, the qualifications to be possessed by persons engaged in the training of
26 career and technical education teachers.
27 10. To coordinate new and existing farm management programs offered by any state
28 agency or entity.
29 11. To create and expand marketing clubs as adjuncts to new and existing farm
30 management programs.
